definition: easy/amiable/to change/to exchange/prefix corresponding to the English adjective suffix "-able" or "-ible"
surname Yi/abbr. for 易經|易经[Yi4 jing1], the Book of Changes
Slovakia/Slovak/abbr. for 斯洛伐克[Si1 luo4 fa2 ke4]
content/calm/still/quiet/safe/secure/in good health/to find a place for/to install/to fix/to fit/to bring (a charge against sb)/to pacify/to harbor (good intentions)/security/safety/peace/ampere
that/those/then (in that case)/commonly pr. [nei4] before a classifier, esp. in Beijing

pinyin: Lu4 yi4 si1 an1 na4 zhou1

sentences.english: A laughing gull coated in heavy oil is seen in the water on East Grand Terre Island, Louisiana
sentences.chinese: 路易斯安那东格兰德岛，海中一只笑鸥裹满石油。

sentences.english: In Louisiana, we have pre-positioned supplies in advance of this year's hurricane season.

路易斯安那沙拉，还有可口的牛排。

sentences.chinese: 路易斯安那猫岛，褐鹈鹕飞过粘上斑斑石油的围油栏。

sentences.english: I saw in Lousiana a live-oak growing.
sentences.chinese: 在路易斯安那我看到一颗橡树生长。
